, tables, and illustrations. One section discusses program notes, while others explain the requirements for submitting manuscripts and electronic files, and outline best practices for student writers. An appendix lists common problem words. Updates include greatly simplified citations of Internet locators, the recognition of multiple platforms, and the expectation of paperless transmission and storage of work. Cited as the authority by The Chicago Manual of Style, this classic handbook is the go-to source for anyone writing about music.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aMUSIC / Reference.2bisacsh  aauthors.  abibliography.  achicago manual of style.  acinema.  acitation rules.  aconcert producers.  aeditors.  ajazz.  amusic criticism.  amusic critics.  amusic historians.  amusic history.  amusic in print.  amusic scholars.  amusic students.  amusic studies.  amusic writers.  amusic writing.  amusical discourse.  amusicians.  amusicology.  anonfiction guide.  apopular music.  aprogram notes.  aprose writing.  areference guide.  arock music.  astudent writers.  astyle guide.  atextbooks.  aworld music.  awriting resource.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028153040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095881440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520958814423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520958814/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY